##------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Docker Build Context Exclusions
#
# This template's Dockerfile bind-mounts the project at runtime (see compose.yml)
# and never COPYs source files into the image, so the simplest correct .dockerignore
# is to exclude everything — the build context stays minimal and image cache
# invalidation is driven solely by Dockerfile contents.
#
# If you later add a stage that COPYs source (e.g. a production image),
# replace the `**` line with the inversion pattern below to whitelist what
# actually belongs in the build context:
#
#   *
#   !/bin/
#   !/composer.json
#   !/composer.lock
#   !/src/
##------------------------------------------------------------------------------
**
